Protesters, who claimed to be operating under the banner of the “Coloured community”, marched from the District Six Museum to Parliament Building in Cape Town on Friday to urge government to “honour their agreement” in the group’s removal from District Six in 2006.

Protesters marched in Uitenhage towards one of the hospital’s administration offices on Tuesday afternoon, demanding that politicians resolve their differences over preferred HIV/AIDS treatment guidelines. “It is the responsibility of our elected officials to take charge and to facilitate measures that will ensure the delivery of quality services for patients,”…

Unrest and violence has once again rocked the Somali capital Mogadishu after heavy fighting erupted Tuesday in the country's capital. Al Shabab fighters said today they were evicting troops from a training camp after a deadly assault on Allied Somali Government troops.
